          { type:"single",
            stem:"[進階] semantic search 與 lexical (BM25) search 各適合什麼？",
            stem_en:"[Advanced] What are semantic search and lexical (BM25) search each best suited for?",
            A:"semantic search 適合語意相近但用詞不同的查詢（如『腦中風』vs 'cerebral infarction'）；BM25 適合 exact-match 關鍵字（如 gene symbol BRCA1、特定 PMID、稀有專有名詞），混合（hybrid）效果通常最佳", A_en:"Semantic search suits semantically-similar but lexically-different queries (e.g., 'brain stroke' vs 'cerebral infarction'); BM25 suits exact-match keywords (gene symbols like BRCA1, specific PMIDs, rare terms); hybrid usually wins",
            B:"兩者完全等價", B_en:"They are equivalent",
            C:"semantic search 永遠優於 BM25", C_en:"Semantic search always beats BM25",
            D:"BM25 已過時", D_en:"BM25 is obsolete",
            ans:"A",
            exp:"在生醫檢索中此區分尤為重要：基因名（BRCA1）、藥物名、PMID、UniProt ID 等 BM25 召回更可靠；而概念性查詢（『causes of inflammation』）embedding 較好。Hybrid search（如 Elastic 的 RRF 融合、Pinecone hybrid mode）結合兩者並 reciprocal rank fusion 重排，是 2024–2025 RAG 最佳實踐。純 embedding 在 OOV gene symbol 上常失敗（BLEU-type evaluation 顯示）。",
            exp_en:"This split matters in biomedical retrieval: BM25 recalls gene names (BRCA1), drugs, PMIDs, UniProt IDs more reliably; embeddings excel at conceptual queries ('causes of inflammation'). Hybrid search (Elastic's RRF, Pinecone hybrid) with reciprocal rank fusion is 2024–2025 RAG best practice. Pure embedding fails on OOV gene symbols (per BLEU-type evaluations)." },
          { type:"single",
            stem:"[進階] 關於 HyDE（Hypothetical Document Embeddings, Gao et al. 2023）對 retrieval 的影響，下列敘述最正確？",
            stem_en:"[Advanced] How does HyDE (Hypothetical Document Embeddings, Gao et al. 2023) affect retrieval?",
            A:"先用 LLM 生成一個『假設的答案 / 假設文檔』，再用該文檔的 embedding 去檢索；可彌補 query 過短或詞彙與 corpus 差異大的問題，但若 LLM 幻覺則 retrieval 也失準", A_en:"First have an LLM generate a 'hypothetical answer/document', then use its embedding for retrieval; bridges short queries or vocabulary gaps with the corpus, but LLM hallucinations corrupt retrieval too",
            B:"它直接修改向量資料庫", B_en:"It directly modifies the vector database",
            C:"它不需要 LLM", C_en:"It doesn't need an LLM",
            D:"它只能用於圖像", D_en:"It's image-only",
            ans:"A",
            exp:"HyDE 的核心：用戶查詢通常太短、用詞不一定接近 corpus；讓 LLM『假裝知道答案』生成 hypothetical doc，其 embedding 與 corpus 中真實答案 embedding 更接近。對 zero-shot 檢索常提升 5–15%。但 trade-off：(1) 多一次 LLM 呼叫成本；(2) LLM 幻覺會誤導；(3) domain-specific corpus 可能反而拉偏。實務上常與 reranker 結合，作為候選召回擴張。",
            exp_en:"Insight: user queries are often too short and don't match corpus vocabulary; making an LLM 'pretend to know' generates a hypothetical doc whose embedding is closer to true corpus answers. Boosts zero-shot retrieval 5–15%. Trade-offs: (1) extra LLM call cost; (2) hallucinations mislead; (3) domain corpus can drift. Often combined with reranker as candidate expansion." },
          { type:"multi",
            stem:"使用 AI 做 systematic review 時，下列哪些是『必要的人類審核步驟』？（多選）",
            stem_en:"When using AI for systematic review, which are necessary human-review steps? (Multiple)",
            A:"PRISMA flow diagram 的 inclusion/exclusion 決策必須有人類最終確認", A_en:"PRISMA inclusion/exclusion decisions must have human final confirmation",
            B:"AI 抽取的 PICO / 樣本量 / outcomes 必須隨機抽樣回讀原 PDF 驗證（≥10–20%）", B_en:"AI-extracted PICO/sample size/outcomes must be randomly spot-checked against the original PDF (≥10–20%)",
            C:"risk of bias 評估（如 Cochrane RoB 2）必須由人類執行，AI 僅輔助", C_en:"Risk-of-bias assessment (e.g., Cochrane RoB 2) must be human-executed, AI only assists",
            D:"final qualitative/quantitative synthesis 與 forest plot 解讀必須由人類完成", D_en:"Final qualitative/quantitative synthesis and forest plot interpretation must be done by humans",
            ans:["A","B","C","D"],
            exp:"四者皆為 Cochrane Handbook、PRISMA 2020、JBI 都要求的人類監督。AI 在 SR 中可加速 (1) 初篩、(2) 結構化抽取、(3) 語言翻譯；但 critical appraisal、PICO 邊界判斷、bias 評估、synthesis 仍必須人類負責。許多期刊（BMJ、JCE）2024+ 規定 AI 輔助 SR 須揭露 + 報告 inter-rater agreement vs AI vs human。",
            exp_en:"All four are required by Cochrane Handbook, PRISMA 2020, JBI. AI accelerates (1) initial screening, (2) structured extraction, (3) translation; but critical appraisal, PICO boundary judgment, bias assessment, and synthesis remain human responsibility. Many journals (BMJ, JCE) 2024+ require AI disclosure + inter-rater agreement reporting (AI vs human)." },
          { type:"tf",
            stem:"是非題：Elicit 等 AI 自動產生的論文摘要可直接複製貼到自己的 paper 中作為背景介紹。",
            stem_en:"True/False: AI-auto-generated paper summaries (e.g., from Elicit) can be directly copied into your paper as background.",
            ans:"F",
            exp:"絕對不可，理由多重：(1) 抄襲風險 — 即便是 AI 摘要也是基於原文，未引用為 plagiarism；(2) 準確性 — AI 摘要可能誤解、過度簡化或編造；(3) ICMJE 規範 — 投稿時若包含 AI 生成內容必須揭露；(4) Nature/Science 等期刊對 AI-generated text 有嚴格限制。正確做法：以 AI 摘要為起點，回讀原文、自己重述、用 Zotero 引用、揭露 AI 輔助。",
            exp_en:"Absolutely not, for multiple reasons: (1) plagiarism risk — AI summaries are based on original text; uncited = plagiarism; (2) accuracy — summaries may misinterpret, oversimplify, or fabricate; (3) ICMJE requires AI disclosure; (4) Nature/Science strictly restrict AI-generated text. Right approach: use as starting point, re-read original, write in your own words, cite via Zotero, disclose AI assist." },
          { type:"single",
            stem:"[情境] 一位博士生有 1 個月時間完成關於『CAR-T 治療實體腫瘤』的 systematic review（預估 800 篇 abstract），她預算有限只能用免費工具。考量 PRISMA 流程與 AI 輔助，最合理的工具組合是？",
            stem_en:"[Scenario] A PhD student has 1 month to complete a systematic review on 'CAR-T for solid tumors' (~800 abstracts) with a tight budget (free tools only). Considering PRISMA and AI assistance, the best tool combo is?",
            A:"PubMed/Embase 結構化檢索 → Rayyan（免費 SR 平台，含 AI 篩選輔助）做初篩 → Elicit 免費額度做結構化抽取 → NotebookLM 上傳通過 full-text screen 的 PDFs 做 cross-paper 比對與 podcast 通勤聽 → Zotero 管理引用 → 全程人工 final review 與 RoB 2 評估", A_en:"PubMed/Embase structured search → Rayyan (free SR platform with AI screening) for initial screen → Elicit free tier for structured extraction → NotebookLM for cross-paper comparison + podcast on commute → Zotero for citation management → human final review and RoB 2 throughout",
            B:"全部用 ChatGPT 跑完", B_en:"Do everything in ChatGPT",
            C:"完全不用 AI，用 Excel 手動", C_en:"No AI at all, do it manually in Excel",
            D:"只看一篇最重要的論文就好", D_en:"Just read the single most important paper",
            ans:"A",
            exp:"A 是 2024–2025 學術社群推薦的免費 SR workflow：(1) Rayyan AI screening 可省 50–70% 時間；(2) Elicit 結構化抽取確保 PICO 完整；(3) NotebookLM grounded-in-source 適合 cross-paper synthesis；(4) Zotero 開源管理；(5) RoB 2 必須人類。每步都有 human-in-the-loop。B 違反 SR 嚴謹性；C 1 個月做 800 篇不可行；D 違反 SR 定義。預估時間：~3 週實際工作。",
            exp_en:"A is the 2024–2025 community-recommended free SR workflow: (1) Rayyan AI screening saves 50–70% time; (2) Elicit ensures PICO completeness; (3) NotebookLM grounded-in-source suits cross-paper synthesis; (4) Zotero is open-source; (5) RoB 2 must be human. Each step has human-in-the-loop. B violates SR rigor; C is infeasible for 800 papers in a month; D violates SR definition. Estimated: ~3 weeks of actual work." }
