            stem_en:"[Advanced] Which best describes MCP's three-layer architecture (host / client / server)?",
            A:"Host 為 LLM-powered 應用（如 Claude Desktop、Cursor）；Client 為 host 內部與單一 server 連線的 connector 實例；Server 為提供 tools/resources/prompts 的外部程式（如 PubMed MCP server）；host 可同時連多個 client→server", A_en:"Host is the LLM-powered app (Claude Desktop, Cursor); Client is the connector instance inside the host that connects to a single server; Server is the external program providing tools/resources/prompts (e.g., PubMed MCP server); a host can run multiple client↔server pairs simultaneously",
