          { type:"tf",
            stem:"是非題：使用任何分割 AI 後，發表時應提供 segmentation 模型版本、後處理參數與 ground-truth 評估方法，確保可重現。",
            stem_en:"True/False: When publishing with segmentation AI, you should report model version, post-processing parameters, and ground-truth evaluation methods for reproducibility.",
            ans:"T",
            exp:"模型版本與後處理會直接影響 metrics；標準 reproducibility 要求皆包含這些資訊。",
            exp_en:"Model version and post-processing directly affect metrics; standard reproducibility expects these to be reported." },
          { type:"single",
            stem:"[進階] 關於 SAM ViT 架構與 Cellpose 流場（flow field）的差異，下列敘述最正確？",
            stem_en:"[Advanced] What is the architectural difference between SAM's ViT and Cellpose's flow field?",
            A:"SAM 用 ViT image encoder + prompt encoder + mask decoder，提供 instance segmentation 但需 prompt（point/box/text）；Cellpose 用 U-Net 預測每像素 horizontal/vertical flow（梯度場指向細胞中心），透過 watershed-like dynamics 合併成 cell instance，無需 prompt 且對 touching cells 表現好", A_en:"SAM uses ViT image encoder + prompt encoder + mask decoder for instance segmentation but needs prompts (point/box/text); Cellpose uses U-Net to predict per-pixel horizontal/vertical flow (gradient field pointing toward cell centers), merging into cell instances via watershed-like dynamics — promptless and handles touching cells well",
            B:"兩者完全相同", B_en:"They are identical",
            C:"SAM 與細胞無關", C_en:"SAM is unrelated to cells",
            D:"Cellpose 不能處理 multi-channel", D_en:"Cellpose cannot handle multi-channel",
            ans:"A",
            exp:"設計哲學差異深刻：(1) SAM (Kirillov et al. 2023 Meta) — generalist, prompt-driven, training on 11M images / 1B masks；(2) Cellpose (Stringer et al. 2021 Nat Methods) — specialist for cells, flow-field 物理模型避免 touching cells 黏連問題；(3) Cellpose-SAM (Pachitariu lab 2024) 融合兩者 — SAM 的 generalization + Cellpose 的 cell-aware decoder。實務：手動 prompt OK → SAM；批次自動 cell counting → Cellpose；mixed → Cellpose-SAM。",
            exp_en:"Deep design philosophy difference: (1) SAM (Kirillov et al. 2023 Meta) — generalist, prompt-driven, trained on 11M images/1B masks; (2) Cellpose (Stringer et al. 2021 Nat Methods) — cell specialist, flow-field physical model avoids touching-cell merging; (3) Cellpose-SAM (Pachitariu lab 2024) fuses both — SAM's generalization + Cellpose's cell-aware decoder. Practice: manual prompts OK → SAM; batch auto cell-counting → Cellpose; mixed → Cellpose-SAM." },
          { type:"single",
            stem:"[進階] 關於 JUMP-Cell Painting benchmark，下列敘述最正確？",
            stem_en:"[Advanced] Which best describes the JUMP-Cell Painting benchmark?",
            A:"JUMP（Joint Undertaking for Morphological Profiling）是 2023+ 多機構合作的大規模 Cell Painting（多通道螢光形態 profiling）資料集，含 > 130,000 化學擾動，用於 phenotypic drug discovery；提供 standardized image preprocessing、feature extraction、model benchmark，是評估 morphology foundation model（如 Phenom）的關鍵 benchmark", A_en:"JUMP (Joint Undertaking for Morphological Profiling) is a 2023+ multi-institutional large-scale Cell Painting (multi-channel fluorescence morphology profiling) dataset with >130,000 chemical perturbations for phenotypic drug discovery; provides standardized image preprocessing, feature extraction, model benchmarks — key for evaluating morphology foundation models (e.g., Phenom)",
            B:"它是一個 RNA-seq benchmark", B_en:"An RNA-seq benchmark",
            C:"它與藥物發現無關", C_en:"Unrelated to drug discovery",
            D:"它是商業 closed dataset", D_en:"A commercial closed dataset",
            ans:"A",
            exp:"JUMP-CP（Chandrasekaran et al. 2024 Nat Methods）是 Broad Institute 主導的『 ImageNet for biology』式倡議：(1) 28 institutions、超過 1M wells；(2) Cell Painting 用 6 種螢光染料覆蓋細胞各 organelle；(3) 化學擾動 + CRISPR genetic 兩類；(4) 公開 model & feature。是訓練 / 評估 cell morphology foundation model（Phenom from Recursion, Bioclip）的金標準。對 phenotypic drug discovery、MOA prediction 是重大資源。",
            exp_en:"JUMP-CP (Chandrasekaran et al. 2024 Nat Methods) is a Broad Institute-led 'ImageNet for biology' initiative: (1) 28 institutions, >1M wells; (2) Cell Painting uses 6 fluorescent dyes covering cellular organelles; (3) both chemical and CRISPR genetic perturbations; (4) public models and features. Gold standard for training/evaluating cell morphology foundation models (Phenom from Recursion, Bioclip). Major resource for phenotypic drug discovery and MOA prediction." },
          { type:"multi",
            stem:"處理 IHC（immunohistochemistry）影像時應注意下列哪些事項？（多選）",
            stem_en:"When processing IHC (immunohistochemistry) images, watch for? (Multiple)",
            A:"染色變異（lot-to-lot、protocol、operator）影響顏色 distribution → 需 stain normalization（如 Macenko, Vahadane）", A_en:"Staining variability (lot, protocol, operator) affects color distribution → need stain normalization (Macenko, Vahadane)",
            B:"H-DAB color deconvolution 分離 hematoxylin 與 DAB 訊號才能準確量化", B_en:"H-DAB color deconvolution separates hematoxylin and DAB signals for accurate quantification",
            C:"訓練 SAM/Cellpose 在 H&E 不一定 transfer 到 IHC；需要 domain-specific fine-tune", C_en:"SAM/Cellpose trained on H&E doesn't always transfer to IHC; needs domain-specific fine-tuning",
            D:"報告 staining protocol、scanner model、normalization method、segmentation tool version 確保 reproducibility", D_en:"Report staining protocol, scanner model, normalization method, segmentation tool version for reproducibility",
            ans:["A","B","C","D"],
            exp:"四者皆 IHC quantification 的核心 challenge：(1) 染色變異是病理 AI 最大 confounder，QuPath / StainTools 提供 normalization；(2) DAB 棕色 + hematoxylin 藍色需 color deconvolution（Ruifrok & Johnston 2001）才能 quantify；(3) H&E vs IHC 顏色分佈差異大，cross-modality transfer 有限；(4) reproducibility 對 PathAI 等 commercial 與學術研究都關鍵。Bankhead et al. QuPath 是免費常用工具。",
            exp_en:"All four are core IHC quantification challenges: (1) staining variability is pathology AI's biggest confounder; QuPath/StainTools provide normalization; (2) brown DAB + blue hematoxylin need color deconvolution (Ruifrok & Johnston 2001) for quantification; (3) H&E vs IHC color distributions differ greatly, cross-modality transfer is limited; (4) reproducibility critical for both commercial (PathAI) and academic research. Bankhead et al.'s QuPath is a free standard tool." },
          { type:"tf",
            stem:"是非題：Cellpose-SAM 已是 universal cell segmentation 解決方案，可直接 zero-shot 用於 IF（immunofluorescence）染色、IHC、cryo-EM 等所有顯微影像而無需 fine-tune。",
            stem_en:"True/False: Cellpose-SAM is the universal cell segmentation solution, directly zero-shot on IF, IHC, cryo-EM, and all microscopy without fine-tuning.",
            ans:"F",
            exp:"錯誤。Cellpose-SAM 確實 generalize 能力大幅提升，但仍有重要限制：(1) zero-shot 在 well-represented modality（brightfield、common IF）很好，但 (2) IHC（DAB chromogen）、cryo-EM（greyscale、低 contrast）、3D lightsheet、spatial transcriptomics image 等 OOD modality 表現仍弱於 fine-tuned specialist；(3) 稀有 cell type、unusual morphology（如神經元 axon、肌肉細胞）仍需 fine-tune；(4) 高密度 touching cells 仍是 hard case。Pachitariu lab 也明確說明這些限制，建議 zero-shot 作為起點，再依需要 fine-tune。",
            exp_en:"False. Cellpose-SAM generalizes much better but still has key limitations: (1) zero-shot is strong on well-represented modalities (brightfield, common IF); (2) IHC (DAB chromogen), cryo-EM (greyscale, low contrast), 3D lightsheet, spatial transcriptomics images are OOD and underperform fine-tuned specialists; (3) rare cell types, unusual morphology (neurons' axons, muscle cells) still need fine-tuning; (4) high-density touching cells remain hard. Pachitariu lab notes these — use zero-shot as starting point, fine-tune as needed." },
          { type:"single",
            stem:"[情境] 一位研究員拍了 200 frame × 100 個發育中胚胎細胞的 3D lightsheet 影片（共 2 TB），想追蹤每個細胞的 lineage 與形態變化。她有單張 A100 80GB GPU。最合理的工具組合是？",
            stem_en:"[Scenario] A researcher captured a 200-frame × 100 developing embryo cell 3D lightsheet movie (2 TB) and wants to track each cell's lineage and morphology. She has a single A100 80GB GPU. Best tool combo?",
            A:"先用 Cellpose-3D（或 StarDist-3D）對每 frame 做 3D segmentation；再用 SAM 2 spatio-temporal tracking 跨 frame 追蹤；用 Mastodon（Fiji plugin）或 LineageTracker 做 lineage tree；3D 可視化用 napari + napari-stress；輸出時記錄所有 model version、preprocessing parameters；A100 80GB 可分批處理（chunk by frame 或 spatial tile）", A_en:"First Cellpose-3D (or StarDist-3D) for per-frame 3D segmentation; then SAM 2 spatio-temporal tracking across frames; Mastodon (Fiji plugin) or LineageTracker for lineage trees; napari + napari-stress for 3D visualization; log all model versions and preprocessing parameters; A100 80GB enables chunked processing (by frame or spatial tile)",
            B:"用 Photoshop 手動標記每個細胞", B_en:"Manually annotate each cell in Photoshop",
            C:"完全不可能", C_en:"Impossible",
            D:"只看一張 frame", D_en:"Look at only one frame",
            ans:"A",
            exp:"developmental lightsheet 是 segmentation + tracking 經典場景：(1) Cellpose-3D / StarDist-3D 處理 isotropic 3D 影像；(2) SAM 2（2024 Meta）原生支援 video 物件追蹤，是 game-changer；(3) Mastodon / LineageTracker 為發育生物學標準 lineage tool；(4) napari 是 modern Python-based 3D viewer，可整合 plugin；(5) 2 TB 資料 chunking 必要，A100 80GB 一次處理 ~16 frame。Keller, Tomer 等 lab 的 BigDataViewer ecosystem 也是選擇。報告版本 + parameter 確保 Stringer 等審稿要求滿足。",
            exp_en:"Developmental lightsheet is a classic segmentation + tracking scenario: (1) Cellpose-3D / StarDist-3D for isotropic 3D images; (2) SAM 2 (2024 Meta) natively supports video object tracking — a game-changer; (3) Mastodon / LineageTracker are standard developmental biology lineage tools; (4) napari is a modern Python-based 3D viewer with plugin integration; (5) 2 TB requires chunking, A100 80GB processes ~16 frames at once. Keller, Tomer lab BigDataViewer ecosystem is another option. Logging versions + parameters meets Stringer-style reviewer requirements." }
